    Gas Pos Demo Request Success Story

    As a gas station owner, I request a demo for the Gas Pos system, so that I can evaluate the solution for enhancing my fuel point of sale operations.

    Success definition: Given I am a gas station owner wanting to see how the Gas Pos system can improve my business When I fill in my email and phone number and submit the demo request Then I should see a confirmation page thanking me for my request, and I should receive further instructions on how to access the demo.

    Reasoning for action: Filling in the email address is crucial to initiate the demo request process for the Gas Pos system. This is a required step to show the system that there is an interested user who wants more information. After entering the email, clicking the 'Watch Gas POS Demo' button submits the form. This action is aligned with the user's goal of requesting a demo to evaluate the solution, getting us closer to the success criteria of receiving a confirmation page.

    Action: fill('d74', 'user@example.com') # Fill in the email address for demo access click('d76') # Click on the 'Watch Gas POS Demo' button to view the demo.

    Change Description: The email address field was filled with 'user@example.com' and then the 'Watch Gas POS Demo' button was clicked, resulting in a transition to an embedded demo interface for the Gas POS system. The new state contains a different iframe for demo content and updates the button options available to the user.

    Reasoning for action: First, I filled in the phone number in the designated textbox (d79) because the request for a demo requires both an email and a phone number as inputs. By entering the phone number, I satisfied the form's requirements, enabling the request to be processed successfully. After completing the phone number entry, I clicked the 'Finish' button (d86) to submit the demo request. This action advances the task significantly as it directly leads towards receiving a confirmation page, thereby achieving the user's goal of requesting a demo.

    Action: fill('d79', '123-456-7890') # Fill in the phone number for demo access click('d86') # Click on the 'Finish' button to submit the demo request.

    Change Description: The browser transitioned from the demo signup page, where the user filled in their phone number and clicked the 'Finish' button, to a thank-you page confirming the demo request. The new page features a prominent heading encouraging users to call for more information and includes buttons for multimedia interaction.
